<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 27 at 5:52PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A Band of Snow is Approaching the Bozeman Area...
Satellite and Radar indicate a band of snow moving southward
across northern Gallatin County and adjacent areas in the
direction of Bozeman. This area of snow could reduce visibility to
a half mile or less. Additionally, gusty winds could make travel
difficult. If you are able to, consider delaying travel over the
next couple hours to allow the snow band to shift south and out of
the Bozeman area.</description>
